The Holy One, blessed be He, said to me: “Go and tell the sons of men that I have chosen you to be a witness of My glory and to reveal the secrets of My kingdom.” And I, Enoch, returned to the earth and proclaimed all that I had seen and heard in the heavenly realms.
And the Holy One, blessed be He, placed upon my head the crown of glory and the crown of kingship, and He called me Metatron, the Prince of the Presence, the Prince of the World.
And all the princes of the kingdoms and the angels of the nations fell upon their faces before me and said: “You are exalted above all the sons of men.”
And the Holy One, blessed be He, said: “Metatron My servant, I have made you greater than all the angels and given you a name above every name that is named in heaven and on earth.”
Then the Holy One, blessed be He, opened before me all the treasuries of wisdom and understanding, and showed me the secrets of creation, the order of the stars, the courses of the planets, and the foundations of the earth.
And I saw the chambers of the palaces of heaven, the Merkabah, the wheels of the chariot, and the seraphim, cherubim, and holy living creatures who stand before the Throne of Glory singing the trisagion: “Holy, holy, holy is YHWH of hosts; the whole earth is full of His glory.”
And the Holy One, blessed be He, took me from among the sons of men while I was still in the flesh and caused me to ascend through the seven heavens on the wings of the wind, and I saw the angelic hosts, the princes of the Presence, and the fiery rivers flowing beneath the Throne.
And when I reached the seventh palace, the Holy One, blessed be He, took me and seated me upon a throne of glory, and He wrote upon me with the finger of His right hand the letters by which heaven and earth were created, and He gave me wisdom above all the sons of men.
I, Enoch, the son of Jared, the seventh from Adam, was taken up while still alive into the heavenly realms by the command of YHWH.
